Algorithms - The future

     I think the way of textures on surfaces will see its end soon
     enough. Generating textures/objects real-time based on algorithms
     will superceed the current defined texture approach.
     Most cards have 32-64MB or memory on them, thats somewhat wasted
     filling it with textures, why not use it to compute things?
     My first thoughts are to randomize the textures within tolerances,
     this will give a hybrid of current texture based approach with
     algorithms.
     In real terms - simply change slightly the textures colour, hue,
     saturation, that type thing. This will give the variation found the
     in the real-world.
     I'm very board with the same 'static' environment found in all
     games.
     Things like trees in games and simulators are usually 2 planes
     perpendicular to each other simply because its not possible to
     render an entire scene of Nvidia Treemark quality trees.
     All done!
       [43]Reply With Quote Reply With Quote [44]Share on Google+
